Construct solid, secure bridges from flimsy popsicles sticks and simple glue. Show off your talent, creativity and dexterity. Can your bridge stand the test of gravity as it takes on unimaginable loads?

Think your ideas have the potential to change the world? Always finding your own solutions more efficient than others? You may just be cut out for Devise, AXIS\'s design competition. Test your mettle against creative minds just like yours in order to come up with the most inspired solutions to the design challenges we give you. A chance to learn and check where you stand among your peers. Demand innovative and ground-breaking solutions. Drive the participants to delve deep into their creative core and emerge with unexpected practical solutions. Devise something new.

Paradeigma is the event to be at if applying your engineering skills to solve problems gives you a high. All you have to do is bring in your skills and design a model to satisfy the given problem statement.
Use your hydraulics knowledge to rotate a turbine by making water pass through several obstacles. Physics was never more fun, especially when you “kind of” get to be Swades’s SRK.

Rockets are the stuff science fiction is made of. Aqua Skylark is where you let the (secret) aerospace engineer in you out. Design a water rocket that “shoots” all of the other competition out of the water.
Robowars is an event in which self - designed robots are made to fight against each other in a battle arena. A crowd favourite, the Robowars battle arena is the place to be at!
Roboticists, listen up! Autobot challenges you to develop a line follower robot which can traverse through the twists and turns of a maze.

In this event participants have to construct/build a manually controlled robot which is capable of grabbing different objects and crossing different types of terrain by reconstructing it\'s path and broken bridge. The obstacles are very challenging and critically test the designing skills of participants.
It is the breathtaking IC engine car racing event of AXIS. This is a perfect place for every car race zealot.

Make a 3D, 2D or Stick Figure Animation video on ‘Time Travel’ or ‘Reaction of Things’, jazz it up with multiple characters and animated effects to showcase your originality and ingenuity to sweep the judges off their feet!
Charge your brain cells as you engage in a one-of-a-kind encryption-decryption battle, and put your problem-solving skills to work to win some very attractive cash prizes!
The all-night coding event is back, with more complex and challenging problems to keep you up all night!

Design a poster using any photo editor on either one of the topics – ‘Life without Essentials’ or ‘Life of a Legend’ and demonstrate your unique interpretation of the problem statement to bag attractive prizes!
Build and design your aquatic robot that can manouevre itself in water to complete all the tasks in this aqua-bot tournament. Ultimate aquatic glory awaits!
Dexter is a nation -wide aptitude test conducted every year for school students. It is a great platform to discover your hidden talents by thinking out of the box.

Bag lucrative industry internships/projects with some of the biggest names in engineering by coming up with creative solutions to the problem statements presented, and gain an insight into how things work in the industrial world.
Come up with out-of-the-box solutions to solve real-world problems faced by NGOs and get a chance to win a social internship at AIESEC.

Techno.docx is a platform for all the budding researchers out there to showcase their original research to engage and captivate, and to get their proposals evaluated by some of the best minds in the industry.
Love debugging electronic circuits and designing new ones? AXIS presents an all new event putting to test your ability to solve a jigsaw puzzle of logic gates and electrical components.
It is one of the most awaited scientific model making competition. It is a unique opportunity for creative thinkers and innovative pioneers.
It is an event where you have to design a catapult to destroy enemy targets. This event aims at developing engineering skills amongst students.
It is an ingenious event to test mathematical skill of school students. They have to solve the most challenging maths problems in a limited time.
One of the most challenging quiz competition for school students. It is a place where the sharpest minds compete to prove themselves the best.
It is a school level simulation of United Nations. It provides students an opportunity to be delegate of a nation.

Gaming has always been a precious pastime to a vast majority of us. Think you\'re an elite gamer? Gamesutra is the event for you. Showcase your gaming skills in the some of the world\'s most played games: Counter Strike, FIFA and NFS.

The Informals at AXIS’15 entertained one and all with the engaging and fun­filled activities. Dodging and shooting with your friends in the paintball arena, getting your hands messy as part of the Colour Wall, instant whacky photography for all the selfie queens and kings, experiencing the future through Google cardboards, robosoccer for the football fans, the informals was the place to be. Yet again, AXIS’16 promises to let you have the time of your lives! So, jump on to the Informals bandwagon at AXIS’16. Stay tuned for more updates.
WallStreet 2016 goes cosmic! Buy shares, sell stock and interact with brokers looking to provide an exchange. Prizes for the tycoon who generates the most revenue!
This is not for the faint-hearted or the anxious. This is the game of leaders. Generate the greatest yield from the resources provided as the CEO of your own company. Dare to take risks.
Freak O Matix, the mathematical challenge dealing with mind-boggling numbers and intricate puzzles is back to bring out the Ramanujan in you!

Experience the most thrilling, innovative and challenging quiz contest you have ever encountered. You will be sent to every corner of the web to cut through the veil of mystery. Take a gander down 221B Baker Street.
A Nagpur citywide quiz contest tailored specifically for all the quizzing enthusiasts out there. So, let’s see if you have the IQ to crack the AQ (AXIS Quiz)!
Come, be a part of an unforgettable psychedelic experience as you put to practice the law of reflection while wielding your laser light sabers! The first ever dark room challenge of AXIS’16.

Android being a robust operating system provides you with stability that has a strong Linux core which helps your android application to withstand the judgment of internet traffic. Android has covered very importance in the mobile industry mostly with our Android applications and developers which then empowers programmers to develop an ingenious mobile application for your android smartphone. This workshop is a comprehensive look at the Android architecture that teaches how to build and deploy applications for Android phones and tablets using the Java programming language. Starting with the installation of the required developer tools, including Eclipse and the Android SDK, the course covers how to build the user interface, work with local data, integrate data from the accelerometer and other sensors, and deploy finished applications to the Play Store

Mobile Phone Building Workshop is an exclusive workshop to learn the entire working of the mobile phone. The importance of a mobile phone is increasing day by day in our lives and this is a golden opportunity to learn the science behind it. The coding and logic gates required to do this workshop will be taught right from the basics on an Arduino processor. The mobile phone will be able to send and receive calls as well as send SMS to anyone. The kit will include an Arduino board, SIM 900A module, LCD display, dialer pad and attached wirings. The basics of automation will be also taught which will be helpful for robotics purposes too.

Ever rode a bike? The art of balancing oneself takes some time to learn. Now learn how to teach this feature to a robot to balance itself in the workshop on a self-balancing robot. This workshop will use gyro sensors and Arduino to balance the unique three tier chassis of the robot. Also learn how to code a bluetooth module to connect to the robot and make it move whilst balancing itself.

Every festival has darker shades to it, an underbelly that is not always visible to the eye. So, is the case with Holi, the festival of colours. AXIS’16, conducted a heart-warming city-wide series called Colours of Nagpur, wherein we brought to light the stories of those who go unnoticed, unheeded working relentlessly as the rest of the city was revelling in the spirit of Holi. Nurses, petrol pump workers, traffic policemen, airport staff, the ‘Coolie’ at the train station, we covered them all. Just a simple act of being a good patient listener showed that we cared.

Addressing the increasing levels of youngsters taking to smoking, AXIS\'16 took social media by storm. All it took for you to show your solidarity for the campaign, was to change your Facebook and Whatsapp profile pictures to the #ISayNoToSmoking poster for a day. With thousands of students across the country volunteering, we hope to have made a small difference among the college campus communities.

Does it sadden you to watch trees being felled only to pave the way to concrete jungles? If it does, the My Tree, My Friend initiative by AXIS\'16 was just the place for you to have been. My Tree, My Friend was a Nagpur city-wide attempt to open the Nagpurian\'s eyes as to how their once green, tree lined city was fast urbanizing into yet another grey, polluted, metropolis. Following on the lines of the friendship day trend of tying ribbons to one’s friends, the students of VNIT instead each befriended a tree by tying a green ribbon around it. The green ribbon, signified a promise of protection in the face of deforestation, from the younger generation to the good old trees whose shade they had grown up under.

The dream that we all hope comes true someday is that there should be no reason to celebrate a day such as World Day against Child Labour. AXIS’16, performed street plays across Nagpur in prime youth hotspots such as malls and parks igniting the fire in the educated youth of the city, to rise and fight against this inhuman and cruel practice. The street plays received an overwhelming response from people of all walks of life.

An atheist turned believer, a banker turned writer, he is a man who rekindled young India\'s fascination for our rich mythology. AXIS, VNIT invites you to an evening with one of India\'s most popular authors Amish Tripathi. Come, live the dream on the 24th of September at VNIT, Nagpur.

For the Third time in India and the First time in Nagpur, AXIS\'16 presents \"AFISHAL\" - The one and only Visual DJ, who has taken DJ\'ing to a new level with the TREMOR. Get ready to Redefine Reality and experience the most incredible Live Show!! Date: 25th September 2016. Time: 6:30pm Venue: VNIT Auditorium Grab your free passes from the AXIS Reception Desk on 24th September from 10:00am. Don\'t forget to get your ID proof while collecting your passes.

We are privileged to have Dr. Ashish Saraf, Vice President,Industry Development, Strategic Partnerships & Offsets, Airbus India as our Chief Guest and Mr. Sachin Kurve, the District Collector of Nagpur as the Guest of Honour. Concluding with a one of a kind Graphic and Beam show, the inaugural evening promises to be a memorable experience! TIME : 23rd September at 5.30 pm in the VNIT Auditorium. Passes available at the AXIS Registration Desk.

Ever seen a bird flying? Replicate the original flying machine in the form of an ornithocopter. This aero-model will flap its mechanical wings using only mechanical energy. The highest quality and lightweight material will help you to fly it to greater heights and distances.
